<item>
            <title>[CXF-6038] Repeatedly invoking setHandlerChain() can cause a build up of handler interceptors on the chain</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-6038</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If an interceptor chain is cached between invocations and a user calls &lt;tt&gt;setHandlerChain()&lt;/tt&gt; before every invocation, the handler chain interceptors get added to the interceptor chain over and over indefinitely.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m guessing that &lt;tt&gt;JaxWsEndpointImpl.addHandlerInterceptors()&lt;/tt&gt; would need to check for the presence of the handler interceptors on the chain already.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
